text.section:
The powers granted to any county pursuant to this section shall not be construed:
To grant to such county powers in any substantive area not otherwise granted to such county by other public general or public local law;
To restrict such county from exercising any power granted to such county by other public general or public local law or otherwise;
To authorize such county or its officers to engage in any activity which is beyond their power under other public general law, public local law or otherwise; or
To preempt or supersede the regulatory authority of any State department or agency under any public general law.
